# room-connect — Project Overview

room-connect is an **interactive web-based 3D connectivity editor**. It lets users load GLTF/GLB 3D scenes, draw axis-aligned bounding box volumes to define walkable areas, and export connectivity graphs as JSON metadata.

## High-level goals

1. Load 3D scenes from GLTF/GLB format and render them interactively via Three.js.
2. Allow users to draw, translate, and scale axis-aligned bounding box volumes in 3D space.
3. Let users name volumes and define connectivity relationships between them.
4. Export the connectivity graph as a structured JSON file.

